It is very important for Arriva to handle the personal data of our passengers and users of our services and applications with care. This privacy statement explains how we process personal data as part of the glimble app.

The glimble app allows you to plan your trip and gives you information about as many transport options as possible, including shared bicycles, shared cars and shared scooters, but also the train, tram, or (water)taxi. After planning your trip, you can use the glimble app to book, pay and use your chosen transport options.

This privacy statement applies when you use the app privately, but also when you use the app for business related travel, or when the app is being offered by your employer.

The party responsible for the processing of your personal data within the meaning of the General Data Protection Regulation (
GDPR
) is Arriva Personenvervoer Nederland B.V. (
Arriva
) (
data controller
), Trambaan 3, 8441BH Heerenveen, The Netherlands and registered with the Dutch Chamber of Commerce under registration number 30124575.

If you have any questions or comments about this privacy statement or about the way in which Arriva processes your data in the context of the glimble app, please feel free to contact us using the contact details below. You can also contact us with questions about the (possible) processing, rectification, restriction of processing, data portability, removal of or access to your data.
0800 – 444 6888
klantenservice@glimble.nl
If you believe that Arriva is not handling your personal data correctly, you can always report this to us. To do so, please contact customer service, see contact details above, or Arriva's Data Protection Officer by e-mail:
fg@arriva.nl
. 

Or by letter:
Arriva Personenvervoer Nederland B.V.
Attn: Data Protection Officer
P.O. Box 626
8440 AP Heerenveen
2. From whom and how do we collect personal data?
Arriva processes personal data of users of the glimble app. If someone other than yourself uses the glimble app on your device, this is not visible for Arriva. We therefore assume that we are only collecting personal data from you.

In the glimble app, it is possible to buy tickets for other travellers, e.g. a child. In doing so, data of persons other than you are collected. We hereby assume that you have received permission to share this personal data with us in the context of purchasing ticket(s). 

The glimble app has an option that enables you to use travel with GPS. This is a non-mandatory, additional option that eliminates the need for travellers to check in and out. Just 'swipe in’ when you start travelling and ‘swipe out’ when you finish your journey. Your journey is composed on the basis of your location data. Please contact customer service using the details at the top of this privacy statement if you have any questions or comments about a journey. 

In the context of the glimble app, Arriva first processes personal data that you provide to us yourself. For example, when installing the glimble app, when using the glimble app, or when contacting us via our glimble customer service or via other channels. In addition, Arriva processes personal data that is collected (automatically) by us when you use the glimble app as described below.  We may also collect personal data about you, for example when you participate in surveys or marketing promotions.
