While using the glimble app, we process data about your
planned, completed and saved trips
. We also process data about your (click) behaviour in the app when using the glimble app. We also process information before, during and after your trip, such as your embarkation and disembarkation locations, means of transport, app behaviour during the trip, tickets, bookings, order status and cancellations in the glimble app. This information can relate to all your actions in the app, and consists of:
a travel number (the unique identifier per journey for the user, the planning, the tickets and the journey made);
the mode of transport you have chosen and the type of transport you have chosen (e.g. shared transport, public transport, private transport);
whether the journey is for business, commuting or private purposes;
possible cancellations of (parts of) your trip;
your starting and ending point of the journey;
the start and end times of the journey;
the costs of the (parts of your) trip;
if you have given consent separately for the MaaS learning environment, we will send the code of the transport provider and the assigned resource number (the latter, if applicable).
A full and up-to-date list of personal data we process while using the glimble app can be viewed
here
.

From the above information (
Travel Information
), we may also derive indirect data about you, which may also qualify as personal data, with regard there to please refer to the
Privacy Statement
. 

Other personal data we process in the context of the glimble app is the personal data you provide to us when you contact us (e.g. when you email us, or contact the customer service).

We also process personal data that we collect through the use of software that is similar to cookies (hereinafter referred to as 'cookie-like' software). For more information about the use of this software in the glimble app and on the website, please refer to our
cookie policy
.

We may combine the various personal data that we process from you, in order to be able to help you better, to improve our services in general, for marketing purposes or to carry out analyses.

We may also ask you to participate in surveys and market studies about the glimble app, where you may be asked to provide personal information.

If you choose not to share certain personal data, this means that the glimble app may not work optimally, or that you may not be able to use certain transport options.
4. On what basis do we process your personal data?
Arriva processes personal data on the basis of one of the four bases below:
1
Execution and establishment of an
agreement
When you want to book a trip via the glimble app, you enter into a transport agreement with the provider of your chosen method of transport. In this context, we may process and share your personal data with this provider and/or with payment service providers and other service providers to the extent necessary to execute the agreement. We also process your personal data in the context of (concluding) the user agreement we have with you for the use of the glimble app, to identify you and to check your age (when using scooters and cars) and to be able to contact you during the term of this user agreement.
If you want to travel using GPS, you enter into an agreement with glimble to process your personal data (including your location), which allows us to determine which journey you made and to charge you your journey afterwards. In this context, we may process and share your personal data with payment service providers and other service providers to the extent necessary for the performance of the agreement. Your data is also used to identify possible fraud, for example if you often deliberately ‘swipe out’ too early.
2
Legal obligation
In certain cases, we are required by law to provide personal data to third parties for purposes outside the scope of our direct services to you. For example, in the event of a suspicion of a serious crime, when data is requested from us by means of a judicial order (which we must comply with). Other examples are the disclosure of data for the implementation of tax legislation, for certain administrative obligations or in the context of requests or investigations by regulators (such as the Dutch Tax and Customs Administration (Belastingdienst), the Dutch Data Protection Authority (Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens) or the Dutch Consumer and Market Authority (Autoriteit Consument en Markt).
3
Legitimate (business)
interest
Our legitimate interests include: optimizing, developing and improving the glimble app (for example by installing and reading cookie-like software as far as allowed without your consent) and the customer experience in the various channels, conducting (statistical) research, security, (crime) prevention, IT management, (market) research into and analysis of our products or services, company management, legal affairs, internal management and debt collection.
4
Or for the cases in which you give us
consent
geeft
When we want to process your location data, namely, to be able to determine your starting point, or to be able to show the walking route to your finishing point;
If we want to provide your personal data to TNO, for research purposes (for more information, see section 8);
If we place certain cookie-like software on your device (for more information about the use of this software, please see our cookie policy, which can be accessed via
this link
and if we want to use your data for marketing purposes, or for purposes other than the use of the glimble app.
5. Withdrawal of consent
If you have given us consent to process the data mentioned in this privacy statement, you can always withdraw your consent.

Withdrawing your consent does not affect the lawfulness of the processing based on the consent given before it was withdrawn.
If at any time you decide that you want to cancel your account, you can do so when you no longer have any outstanding (payment) obligations towards us. You can do this by contacting our customer service, using the contact details at the top of this privacy statement.
6. For what purposes does Arriva process your personal data?
We process your personal data for the purposes listed below. The number behind each purpose corresponds with the basis/bases stated above.
Purposes
