17
Carrying out a driving licence check.
If you want to use a shared scooter or car, we will first establish your identity and check the validity and authenticity of your driving licence (and possibly your identity card or passport). For checking your driving licence, we use the services of our service partner Veriff OÜ (Estonia; hereinafter "Veriff"). Veriff's software is integrated into the glimble app via a Software Development Kit (SDK). During the booking process you are invited to have your driving licence and identity verified. This requires a valid driving licence and a selfie. During the driving licence check Veriff will process your names, date of birth, issue date of your driving licence, expiry date of your driving licence, document number of your driving licence, driving licence type (AM, A, A1, A2, B, BE, B+, etc.), the selfie you took and the mobile device type. Veriff will remove, blur or otherwise make unreadable the personal data or identification documents presented during the verification session which are not necessary for the driving licence check. Veriff's software automatically deletes the photos after 30 days. Arriva does not store the photos in its own systems. A number of designated officials of Arriva do have access to the software of Veriff, so that they can assist if there is a problem. The personal data processed by Veriff in connection with the provision of the driving licence check will be available to Arriva for a period of 90 (ninety) days. Thereafter, the data will be archived by Veriff for a maximum of 18 (eighteen) months and will only be available to Arriva upon request.
3
18
Placing marketing/tracking cookie-like software.
